      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"letting go\" part... it sounds peaceful, but it also sounds so permanent. It's just that every time I look at the horizon, I don't feel excitement for the next stop anymore. I just feel this heavy exhaustion. Like I've reached the end of the map and there's no reason to keep walking into the blank spaces. Does it ever feel like the trip is just... meant to end?",
